
@startuml

' Entities involved in the H2S Pickup and Delivery Service System

package "H2S System" {
    [Resident] as Resident
    [PickupRequest] as PickupRequest
    [Vehicle] as Vehicle
    [VolunteerDriver] as VolunteerDriver
    [PickupRoute] as PickupRoute
    [Item] as Item
    [DistributionCenter] as DistributionCenter
    [Article] as Article
    [RFIDTag] as RFIDTag
    [Category] as Category
    [Employee] as Employee
    [Client] as Client
    [DeliveryService] as DeliveryService
    [FoodBank] as FoodBank
}

' Relationships between classes

Resident --> PickupRequest : places
PickupRequest --> Item : includes
PickupRequest --> Resident : belongs to
PickupRequest --> PickupRoute : assigned to
PickupRoute --> Vehicle : assigned to
PickupRoute --> VolunteerDriver : driven by
Vehicle --> VolunteerDriver : has driver
PickupRoute --> PickupRequest : includes
Item --> PickupRequest : part of
Item --> Article : may be
Item --> FoodBank : goes to directly if food
Article --> RFIDTag : tagged with
Article --> Category : categorized under
Article --> DistributionCenter : delivered to
DistributionCenter --> Employee : managed by
Employee --> Article : inspects and categorizes
Employee --> DeliveryService : arranges
Client --> DeliveryService : requests
DeliveryService --> Article : delivers
DeliveryService --> VolunteerDriver : uses
DeliveryService --> Client : serves
VolunteerDriver --> DeliveryService : may deliver
VolunteerDriver --> PickupRoute : drives

' Attributes and associations

[Resident] : - name
[Resident] : - streetAddress
[Resident] : - phoneNumber
[Resident] : - email (optional)

[PickupRequest] : - requestedDate
[PickupRequest] : - pickupTime (8:00-14:00)
[PickupRequest] : - description

[Item] : - dimensions
[Item] : - weight
[Item] : - type (e.g., second hand, non-perishable food)

[Vehicle] : - capacity
[Vehicle] : - storageSpace

[VolunteerDriver] : - availabilityDays
[VolunteerDriver] : - vehicleAssigned

[PickupRoute] : - startLocation
[PickupRoute] : - endLocation

[Article] : - qualityStatus
[Article] : - originalDescription
[Article] : - correctedDescription

[RFIDTag] : - tagId
[RFIDTag] : - timestampOfTagging

[Category] : - categoryName (from list of 134)

[Client] : - needsCategories
[Client] : - homeAddress

[DeliveryService] : - deliveryDate
[DeliveryService] : - status

[Employee] : - employeeId
[Employee] : - role

@enduml

---

### ✅ Notes:
- This class diagram models the **main actors**, **entities**, and **relationships** from the system requirement.
- It assumes that `Item` can be either an `Article` or a `Non-perishable Food`, with food items going directly to the `FoodBank`.
- The `PickupRoute` is associated with multiple `PickupRequests` and one `Vehicle` driven by a `VolunteerDriver`.
- The `DistributionCenter` handles `Articles`, which are then optionally used for `DeliveryService` to `Clients`.

